description._content: Catalog #: 09_01566 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Elwyn Gibbon (on left) with pilot. Handwritten inscription ""My ship, instructor and myself the day I soloed - August 3 1932. My parachute is pulled up against my back"", Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Tags: Elwyn H.
